&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Older Persons Mental Health Nurse - North Sedgemoor &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for a rewarding job role in the Bridgwater / Burnham area?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you an experienced Registered Mental Health Nurse looking for a new challenge?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a small but friendly Community Mental Health team covering the Bridgwater and Burnham area, and are looking to recruit a motivated Mental Health Nurse or Allied Healthcare professional to join our multi-disciplinary team for 37.5 hours a week Monday to Friday working in a Care Co-ordination role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has an energy and passion for working with older adults, and who would appreciate the opportunity to work alongside colleagues in the wider integrated team of District Nurses and IRT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for managing a caseload of clients, who are subject to the CPA process. This will include both functional and organic illness, as well as spending some weekdays on Duty 9-5am.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be hard working and able to work autonomously as well as work well within a team environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is also a developmental role in which we will fully support you with, and there will be the opportunity to participate in Day Hospital provision for clients and also to undertake Memory Assessments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLouise DavisJob titleTeam ManagerEmail addresslouise.davis@SomersetFT.nhs.ukTelephone number01278 720275Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If unavailable please contact Helen Andrew on 01278 765140&lt;/p&gt;
